      "content": "\"Their very lack of structured thought is what makes them a volatile element, a powder keg of untamed impulse. Without the stabilizing influence of European reason, their passions will inevitably boil over into needless savagery and conflict. They are a force of nature, yes, but a destructive one, and only our disciplined hand can contain that inherent, dangerous wildness for the betterment of all.\"",
      "source": "target",
